{% extends "layouts/base.njk" %}
{% import "partials/_demo.njk" as ui %}

{% block title %}Toasts · Stisla v3{% endblock %}

{% set img_avatar = "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1494790108377-be9c29b29330?auto=format&fit=facearea&facepad=2.5&w=120&h=120&q=80" %}
{% set img_avatar_2 = "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1507003211169-0a1dd7228f2d?auto=format&fit=facearea&facepad=2.5&w=120&h=120&q=80" %}

{% block content %}
  <header>
    <h1>Toasts</h1>
    <p class="lead">A non-blocking notification panel.</p>
  </header>

  <section>
    <h2>Basic</h2>
    <p>A toast is a small surface with a title and a body message. Keep <code>.show</code> for static demos, the framework JS handles it once you trigger a real toast.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="toast show" role="alert" aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true">
      <div class="toast-header">
        Workspace saved
      </div>
      <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="toast" aria-label="Close"></button>
      <div class="toast-body">Your changes to billing details have been written and synced.</div>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Anatomy</h2>
    <p>Padding lives on <code>.toast</code> itself, so the header band and body padding from Bootstrap drop to zero. The layout is a 2-column grid. Col 1 stacks <code>.toast-header</code>, <code>.toast-body</code>, and <code>.toast-action</code>. Col 2 holds <code>.btn-close</code> as a direct child of <code>.toast</code> so it sits in its own cell at the top-right corner.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="toast show" role="alert" aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true">
      <div class="toast-header">
        <i data-lucide="shield-check"></i>
        Two-factor enabled
      </div>
      <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="toast" aria-label="Close"></button>
      <div class="toast-body">Logins to this workspace now require a code from your authenticator app.</div>
      <div class="toast-action gap-3">
        <a href="#" class="link-body-emphasis text-decoration-none">Dismiss</a>
        <a href="#" class="text-decoration-none">Manage devices</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Leading icon</h2>
    <p>Drop an <code>&lt;svg&gt;</code> or <code>&lt;i&gt;</code> as the first child of <code>.toast-header</code>. Use a color utility to cue the message state without tinting the whole surface.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="d-flex flex-column gap-2">
      <div class="toast show" role="status" aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true">
        <div class="toast-header">
          <i data-lucide="check-circle-2" class="text-success"></i>
          Invoice sent
        </div>
        <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="toast" aria-label="Close"></button>
        <div class="toast-body">We emailed the May invoice to billing@acme.co.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="toast show" role="alert" aria-live="assertive" aria-atomic="true">
        <div class="toast-header">
          <i data-lucide="x-circle" class="text-danger"></i>
          Couldn't upload
        </div>
        <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="toast" aria-label="Close"></button>
        <div class="toast-body">Network dropped halfway through. Reconnect and try again.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="toast show" role="status" aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true">
        <div class="toast-header">
          <i data-lucide="triangle-alert" class="text-warning"></i>
          Storage almost full
        </div>
        <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="toast" aria-label="Close"></button>
        <div class="toast-body">You're at 94% of the workspace quota. Archive old exports to free space.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Leading image</h2>
    <p>Swap the icon for an <code>&lt;img&gt;</code> when the source is a person or product. The image keeps its natural size, so reach for <code>.rounded-circle</code> and a width attribute to shape it.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="toast show" role="status" aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true">
      <div class="toast-header">
        <img src="{{ img_avatar }}" alt="" class="rounded-circle" width="28" height="28" />
        Maya Singh
        <span class="text-body-tertiary fw-normal">10 mins ago</span>
      </div>
      <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="toast" aria-label="Close"></button>
      <div class="toast-body">Shared "Q3 roadmap" with you. You have edit access to the document.</div>
      <div class="toast-action gap-3">
        <a href="#" class="link-body-emphasis text-decoration-none">Dismiss</a>
        <a href="#" class="text-decoration-none">Open file</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Action row</h2>
    <p>Add <code>.toast-action</code> below the body for inline links or buttons. The row sits at the root's left padding edge, aligned with the leading slot above. For ghost buttons, add <code>.btn-flush-start</code> so the label text lines up with the body above instead of the button frame.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="d-flex flex-column gap-2">
      <div class="toast show" role="status" aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true">
        <div class="toast-header">
          <i data-lucide="user-plus" class="text-primary"></i>
          Sara Lin invited you
        </div>
        <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="toast" aria-label="Close"></button>
        <div class="toast-body">You've been added to the Q3 Roadmap workspace as an editor.</div>
        <div class="toast-action">
          <button type="button" class="btn btn-sm btn-ghost-secondary btn-flush-start">Decline</button>
          <button type="button" class="btn btn-sm btn-primary">Accept</button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="toast show" role="status" aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true">
        <div class="toast-header">
          <i data-lucide="trash-2"></i>
          Project moved to trash
        </div>
        <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="toast" aria-label="Close"></button>
        <div class="toast-body">"Redesign" will be deleted in 30 days.</div>
        <div class="toast-action">
          <button type="button" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-secondary">Undo</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Stacked container</h2>
    <p>Wrap several toasts in <code>.toast-container</code> to stack them. Pair with positioning utilities (<code>.position-fixed</code>, <code>.top-0</code>, <code>.end-0</code>) when you mount it on the page.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="toast-container position-static p-0">
      <div class="toast show" role="status" aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true">
        <div class="toast-header">
          <img src="{{ img_avatar_2 }}" alt="" class="rounded-circle" width="28" height="28" />
          Mateo Reyes
          <span class="text-body-tertiary fw-normal">just now</span>
        </div>
        <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="toast" aria-label="Close"></button>
        <div class="toast-body">Started a follow-up thread on the auth migration. Tagged you.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="toast show" role="status" aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true">
        <div class="toast-header">
          <i data-lucide="bell" class="text-primary"></i>
          Daily summary ready
        </div>
        <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="toast" aria-label="Close"></button>
        <div class="toast-body">12 tickets closed, 4 opened, 2 awaiting your review.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="toast show" role="status" aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true">
        <div class="toast-header">
          <i data-lucide="check-circle-2" class="text-success"></i>
          Deploy succeeded
        </div>
        <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="toast" aria-label="Close"></button>
        <div class="toast-body">api v1.42.0 is live on production.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Without leading slot</h2>
    <p>The leading slot is optional. Drop it and the header reads as a plain title row.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="toast show" role="status" aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true">
      <div class="toast-header">
        Saved as draft
      </div>
      <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="toast" aria-label="Close"></button>
      <div class="toast-body">Your post is private until you publish it.</div>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Trigger</h2>
    <p>Bootstrap ships the toast as opt-in JS. Mount the markup once inside a <code>.toast-container</code>, then call <code>.show()</code> on the instance to reveal it. The container fixes the toast to a corner of the viewport.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary" data-demo-toast="#trigger-toast">Show toast</button>
    <div class="toast-container position-fixed top-0 end-0 p-3">
      <div class="toast fade" id="trigger-toast" role="status" aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true">
        <div class="toast-header">
          <i data-lucide="link" class="text-success"></i>
          Link copied
        </div>
        <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="toast" aria-label="Close"></button>
        <div class="toast-body">Anyone with the link can view the page.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}

    <p>The button above uses a site-only <code>data-demo-toast</code> attribute to fire the toast. In your own code, grab the element and call the API directly.</p>
    {% call ui.code(lang='js', title='trigger.js') %}
    const el = document.querySelector('#trigger-toast');
    const toast = Stisla.bs.Toast.getOrCreateInstance(el, {
      autohide: true,
      delay: 4000,
    });
    toast.show();
    {% endcall %}
  </section>
{% endblock %}
